Hungary to Reduce Debt This Year, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-04-15T07:31:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/hungary-to-reduce-debt-this-year-handelsblatt-says-correct-.html
(Corrects budget deficit to debt in headline, first
paragraph.)  Hungary aims to reduce its
government debt this decade to 50 percent of gross domestic
product from 80 percent, Handelsblatt reported, citing Foreign
Minister Janos Martonyi.  While Hungary plans to join the euro area, it is too early
to say when, the Dusseldorf-based newspaper quoted him as saying
in an interview published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  